</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
CASIO Computer, the leading Japanese digital watchmaker, announced a 39.6
per cent fall, to Y11.5bn (Dollars 103.60m), in pre-tax profit for the year
ended in March. It blamed the decline on the rapid appreciation of the yen
in recent months.
