<HEADLINE>
FT  19 MAY 93 / UK Company News: Diploma shows improvement to Pounds 8.1m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PETER PEARSE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
DIPLOMA, the electronics, building products and special steels group, lifted
pre-tax profits from Pounds 2.5m to Pounds 8.1m in the six months to March
31.
However, the advance was flattered by the restating of last time's figures
to conform with FRS 3 accounting standards.
As reported, the previous profits emerged at Pounds 6.2m; restated, the
losses of Pounds 1.1m on a disposal and Pounds 2.6m on goodwill have now
become exceptional charges.
Mr Christopher Thomas, chairman, said that the six months under review had
been one of 'two contrasting quarters, with considerably greater buoyancy in
the more recent period'.
He said that 'the worst of the long, deep recession appears to be over, if
our own experience over the last few months is indicative'.
As previously, there were two star performers.
Macro, the active components distributor, made profits of Pounds 3.2m on
turnover of Pounds 29m out of the electronic division's Pounds 5.7m and
Pounds 49m totals. It lifted its own profits and sales 75 per cent and 35
per cent respectively.
Mr Thomas added that the smaller Nortronic also performed well, with profits
up 50 per cent.
The other star was IG Lintels, which made Pounds 2.5m of the building
products division's Pounds 2.7m, though the first quarter had been
'unexciting'.
However loss-making Norwood Partitions had to be reorganised and its
workforce halved to 30, resulting in an exceptional debit of Pounds 1.1m.
Again oil sector uncertainty affected steels, though the reorganised H
Whitham increased profitability.
Group turnover was Pounds 74m (Pounds 61.9m) and operating profits Pounds
8.5m (Pounds 5.1m). The interim dividend is hoisted to 3.5p (2.75p), payable
from earnings per share of 10.7p (7.3p).
</TEXT>
