<HEADLINE>
FT  19 MAY 93 / Confidence in property sees upturn
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By VANESSA HOULDER, Property Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
CONFIDENCE IN the UK commercial property market has risen sharply in the
last three months, according to a poll by Gallup for CSW, a property
magazine.
It found that 94 per cent of the 100 property companies and institutional
investors polled believed that the market would show some improvement in the
next 12 months.
Some 17 per cent of respondents thought that a 'meaningful recovery' had
already started or would happen later this year, compared with 5 per cent in
January.
But 55 per cent of those polled did not expect recovery until next year and
28 per cent expected no revival to take place until 1995 or later.
The survey covered 100 property investors and companies owning nearly Pounds
60bn of property assets.
