FT  19 MAY 93 / Airline seeks extra US route
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
DELTA AIRLINES has applied for authority to fly between Manchester and New
York's Kennedy Airport, a route operated by British Airways and American
Airlines.
Earlier this month Continental, another US carrier, applied for a licence
for the route from Manchester to Newark, New Jersey, a route Virgin Atlantic
is considering applying for.
Manchester Airport said yesterday that four other new routes were under
serious consideration by US carriers. American, which flies daily from
Manchester to Chicago and New York, is looking at Miami and Dallas as new
destinations, while United Airlines is considering Washington, and Northwest
Airlines has its eye on Detroit.
