the US as a precaution against the imposition of sanctions, it said when
announcing its results.
Among Allied-Lyons' products that would have been hit was Courvoisier
cognac. 'Resolution of the Gatt agreement is important to us,' said Mr
Michael Jackaman, chairman. Allied-Lyons also hoped that European
governments would stop penalising spirits when setting duties on alcohol.
