FT  19 MAY 93 / Argentina and Brazil say they support Japan's UN bid
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TOKYO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Foreign ministers of Argentina and Brazil said yesterday they supported
Japan's bid for a permanent seat on the United Nations Security Council as
part of overall reform of the council, AP reports from Tokyo. 'We told Japan
that our countries support its membership. . ,' said Mr Fernando Henrique
Cardoso, Brazil's foreign minister. 'We also believe it is important to
include representation from developing countries, including Latin America.'
