<TEXT>
WORK WAS resumed at Danish slaughterhouses yesterday after they were
paralysed by a three-week strike of 16,000 workers, writes Hilary Barnes in
Copenhagen.
The workers won the right never to work more than 37 hours a week but they
expect to be doing substantial overtime in the next few weeks to make up the
back log of pigs waiting for slaughter caused by the strike.
