<HEADLINE>
FT  18 MAY 93 / World Commodities Prices: Tea
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
There was improved demand for brighter teas, reports the Tea Brokers'
Association. Landed best east Africans and coloury medium sorts were fully
firm and often 3-5p dearer, particularly PD's. Plainer descriptions were
irregularly easier. Ceylons met less demand at easier rates. Offshore:
brighter Kenya and Zimbabwe teas were often 5-8p dearer but plainer Africans
met selective demand at often easier rates. Quotations: quality 165p/kg,
good medium 124p/kg, medium 110p/kg, low medium 87p/kg. The highest price
realised this week was 167p for a Rwanda pf. 1.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>GBZ  United Kingdom, EC.
</CN>
<XX>
Industries:-
</XX>
