FT  18 MAY 93 / International Company News: Sintokogio announces pre-tax
profits
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Sintokogio, Japan's leading maker of casting machines, announced its pre-tax
profits declined sharply for the financial year to March 1993.
Pre-tax profits dropped by 47.9 per cent from a year earlier on lower
product prices amid sluggish demand and higher personnel expenses. Sales
eased by 17.6 per cent at 41.2bn.
The Nagoya-based company expected a sharp 58.8 per cent drop in its pre-tax
profits to Y1.4bn for the current year due to a predicted decrease in plant
investment.
Sales are expected to decrease by 10.3 per cent to Y37bn this year.
