fell 8.1 per cent to SKr2.92bn and total income dropped to SKr3.90bn from
SKr4.01bn. However, a cost-cutting drive reduced operating expenses by 14
per cent to SKr1.99bn and helped the operating result before credit losses
to improve to SKr1.91bn from SKr1.69bn.
