SWEDBANK, the newly-merged savings bank group, reports a sharp reduction in
first-quarter losses, writes Christopher Brown-Humes in Stockholm. Operating
deficit fell to SKr864m (Dollars 118m) from SKr2.94bn after loan losses of
SKr2.78bn against SKr4.63bn. The comparative figures represent one quarter
of 1992 totals.
