FT  18 MAY 93 / UK Company News: Pilkington wins Chrysler contract
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KEVIN DONE, Motor Industry Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
PILKINGTON, the UK glassmaker, has won a five-year contract to supply
automotive privacy glass to Chrysler, the US vehicle maker.
The deal is understood to be worth around Dollars 100m and covers the supply
of a new product, Galaxsee, developed jointly by Pilkington in the UK and by
Libbey-Owens-Ford, its 80 per cent owned US subsidiary.
Nippon Sheet Glass of Japan owns a 20 per cent stake in the US operation.
The privacy glass will be fitted in some Chrysler fourwheel drive
leisure/utility vehicles such as the Grand Cherokee and in some of its
minivan/people carrier vehicles such as the Chrysler Voyager/Dodge Caravan.
The glass will be manufactured at the Libbey-Owens-Ford plant near Toledo,
Ohio.
Pilkington expects to market the product in Europe in particular in southern
European countries.
