<HEADLINE>
FT  18 MAY 93 / Observer: Liquid assets
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Surely something wrong with the City of London's sense of values? Of the 293
Square Mile banking jobs listed by Day Associates' latest pay survey, only
three carry average salaries of less than Pounds 10,000 whereas 13 are above
the Pounds 100,000 mark.
There's no prize for guessing that the best rewarded is the big branch
general manager, averaging Pounds 161,506 in salary which is typically
boosted by bonuses to Pounds 192,518. But who, apart from newly recruited
school leavers, d'you suppose is at the other end of the scale?
The tea lady with an average salary of Pounds 9,450 plus a measly bonus of
Pounds 160.65. That rates a general manager as worth more than 20 tea ladies
whereas, measured by their respective effects on staff morale, the ratio is
more probably the other way round.
</TEXT>
